          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The morphological opening of an image is defined as an erosion followed by a dilation. Opening can remove small bright spots (i.e. \"salt\") and connect small dark cracks. This tends to \"open\" up (dark) gaps between (bright) features."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
